1
00:00:04,000 --> 00:00:07,000
♬〜

2
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:13,000
♬〜

3
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:16,000
ᗒ(Men's yells)

4
00:00:16,000 --> 00:00:25,000
♬〜

5
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:27,000
(Man) Hey, there you are! It's over there!

6
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:29,000
(Men's yells)

7
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:51,000
♬〜

8
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:53,000
(Norifumi Akase) Good morning.

9
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:55,000
(Shiori Akase) Good morning. (Akase Mahoro) Good morning.

10
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Mahoro, do you want to go out somewhere today?

11
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,000
(Mahoro) Um... after this is finished.

12
00:01:02,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Ah, I see. That's right. Yeah.

13
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
(Shiori) It's been a while. Good night.

14
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
No, the Health and Welfare Division will be taking paid leave.

15
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:17,000
Hey. Did you buy it? game.

16
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:21,000
(Shiori) No. My brother-in-law sent it to Mahoro.

17
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,000
My brother?

18
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,000
Why? It's not even my birthday.

19
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:31,000
here we go…. You knew exactly what Mahoro wanted.

20
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:36,000
(Shiori) Please say thank you.

21
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:40,000
Have you met your brother-in-law recently?

22
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
(Shiori) Mahoro, let's eat. (Mahoro) Yes.

23
00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:49,000
I'll enjoy having this.

24
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:59,000
♬〜

25
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,000
🔊(Announcement) This is the Mobile Investigation Division of the National Police Agency.

26
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:13,000
🔊At the exciting police day that will be held tomorrow, there will be a traffic safety experience session for police...

27
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
(Kozawa Tsubame) When there are no incidents, you also do public relations activities.

28
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:20,000
(Hiroshi Shiratori) We need to make effective use of trucks. It costs money to maintain it.

29
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,000
Do you keep turning right and going around in circles?

30
00:02:23,000 --> 00:02:26,000
Basics of advertising cars.

31
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:29,000
If you stop in the right turn lane, you'll see someone waiting at a traffic light. (camera shutter sound)

32
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:31,000
You can see it!

33
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:33,000
(Swan) That's what it is. Okay...!

34
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:38,000
Photos are posted on SNS. (Swan) Right?

35
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:41,000
It's a waste of tax money!

36
00:02:42,000 --> 00:02:47,000
🔊(Announcement) The National Police Agency's new mascot, Patota, will also appear.

37
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:55,000
(Hiroe) Help!

38
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:57,000
Huh? (Swan) What happened?

39
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,000
(Hiroe) Hahahahahahaha….

40
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:04,000
You're a police officer, right? Please help! What happened?

41
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:06,000
I'm being chased!

42
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:08,000
(Men's yells)

43
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:10,000
Wow! bud!

44
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,000
Please ride! yes.

45
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:18,000
please.

46
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:23,000
Mr. Shiratori, let me out! (Swan) Yes! It’s here, it’s here!

47
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,000
Ah, here it is for now... yes.

48
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Belt please. yes.

49
00:03:32,000 --> 00:03:34,000
(sound of fastening seatbelt)

50
00:03:38,000 --> 00:03:41,000
<This story is about seven unique detectives.>

51
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:47,000
This is a drama about a moving investigation headquarters vehicle, commonly known as Ichibanboshi, that solves cases.

52
00:03:56,000 --> 00:04:00,000
(Men's yells)

53
00:04:03,000 --> 00:04:15,000
♬〜

54
00:04:15,000 --> 00:04:18,000
(Momoko Nakazawa) Ah... it's so hot!

55
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,000
I want to hand out flyers and drink beer soon!

56
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:27,000
who? Huh... who?

57
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:31,000
Being chased by some creepy-looking guys... Ah, please sit down.

58
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:33,000
Sorry.

59
00:04:37,000 --> 00:04:39,000
We are from the Mobile Investigation Division.

60
00:04:39,000 --> 00:04:43,000
There's a police PR event tomorrow, so I'll be waiting here for a while.

61
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:46,000
May I know your name?

62
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:49,000
My name is Hiroe Nakamura.

63
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Hiroe Nakamura….

64
00:04:51,000 --> 00:05:00,000
♬〜

65
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:03,000
(Swan) Hello. Hello.

66
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:06,000
Hello.

67
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,000
I was surrounded by scary men.

68
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:14,000
Nakamura-san, why are you being chased?

69
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:20,000
You... you look like a celebrity.

70
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:25,000
A murderer's wife...

71
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
The murderer's wife?

72
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:32,000
8 years ago→

73
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Hiroe Nakamura was born into a wealthy family →

74
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:42,000
She married her husband, a major banker, had a child, and lived a happy life.

75
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:47,000
All of a sudden, that everyday life came crashing down.

76
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Where is your husband? where are you?

77
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:58,000
(Momoko's voice) Hiroe is shocked to hear her husband's face behind the scenes.

78
00:05:58,000 --> 00:06:01,000
My husband is addicted to illegal casinos →

79
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:07,000
He borrowed more than 100 million yen from a black market dealer and melted it all down.

80
00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:11,000
Hiroe, who believed that her husband was serious and didn't know anything, →

81
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:14,000
I couldn't accept the fact.

82
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:20,000
Before I knew what was going on, the police came...

83
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:25,000
(Investigator) Your wife and husband are suspects in a murder case.

84
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:28,000
Do you really not know where he ran away?

85
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:32,000
(Hiroe's voice) My husband committed robbery to pay off his debt →

86
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:36,000
He killed three members of the family who lived there.

87
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:40,000
One is still a small child.

88
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:51,000
♬〜

89
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:55,000
📞(Male) Check it out. Is it your husband's watch?

90
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:59,000
Where is my husband?

91
00:06:59,000 --> 00:07:05,000
📞(Male) Found it before the police and sunk it in Tokyo Bay. I'll never find it.

92
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:10,000
📞My husband didn't get a single yen from killing people.

93
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,000
📞I'll give it back to you instead.

94
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:17,000
(Yuki Nakamura) Mom.

95
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:20,000
What about daddy? Why aren't you coming back?

96
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:31,000
Yuuki... Daddy...

97
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:39,000
(sob)

98
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:41,000
Didn't you talk to the police?

99
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:43,000
It's written in the article.

100
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:49,000
Debt collectors usually know that the police can't intervene.

101
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:54,000
The internet was buzzing and the location was identified, right?

102
00:07:55,000 --> 00:08:00,000
(Hiroe) Her real name and address were revealed, and her face photo was also exposed...

103
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:04,000
I kind of remember this incident.

104
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:08,000
Lots of writing...

105
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:11,000
why?

106
00:08:11,000 --> 00:08:15,000
Your husband may have committed a crime, but that doesn't mean your family is at fault!

107
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:19,000
(Swan) That argument doesn't work on the internet.

108
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:22,000
I hate the internet! Shit! (sound of tapping on desk)

109
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:26,000
ah….

110
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:31,000
Momoko-san: I was sent to the first star because the internet went up in flames...

111
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:37,000
ᗕ(Sound of hitting a truck)

112
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:40,000
Huh? what? (Swan) Wow...

113
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:48,000
(sound of tapping)

114
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Sigh… Just take a look. Huh?

115
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:58,000
If this gets spread, please go to the top and protest.

116
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,000
(Swan's Sigh)

117
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:07,000
(sound of truck hitting)

118
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,000
(Male) Hey! Wait a minute.

119
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:14,000
(Male) Hey, what is it? Teme!

120
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:20,000
Get close to the target. Take a photo.

121
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:25,000
Check with the database.

122
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,000
(Teruhiko Nemoto) Do you have time for that?

123
00:09:27,000 --> 00:09:29,000
Stop researching people! I'm busy too!

124
00:09:29,000 --> 00:09:32,000
I'm working on my day off! You get it!

125
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,000
(clicks tongue)

126
00:09:35,000 --> 00:09:38,000
(Yu Masuda) Nemoto-senpai, is it okay like this?

127
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:41,000
(Nemoto) Why are we doing this...!

128
00:09:41,000 --> 00:09:43,000
This is also a police officer's job.

129
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:45,000
(Basically) I don't admit it!

130
00:09:45,000 --> 00:09:48,000
(Masuda) How neatly do you arrange the confiscated items →

131
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:52,000
The Metropolitan Police Department and each prefectural police department are competing.

132
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:54,000
Then we can't lose! yes.

133
00:09:58,000 --> 00:10:02,000
This criminal... why did he only steal socks?

134
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:09,000
♬〜

135
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:11,000
Hey!

136
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:19,000
(Men's laughter)

137
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:26,000
It's scary, I thought I'd hit it.

138
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:28,000
Thank you for your hard work.

139
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:31,000
Sorry for the day off. (Suguro Hanji) What are you doing?

140
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:35,000
Handing out road safety flyers. The children will be happy.

141
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:39,000
(Mio Amao) I heard about the situation. Is there a need to get together even though it's not an incident?

142
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:41,000
(sigh)

143
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:45,000
So, are you being chased by men outside?

144
00:10:45,000 --> 00:10:48,000
Apparently it's been 8 years. Eight years...?

145
00:10:48,000 --> 00:10:52,000
The men are a group of semi-grays who set up their nest in Roppongi.

146
00:10:52,000 --> 00:10:57,000
He says he was hired by a black money businessman to chase her to pay off a debt of 100 million yen.

147
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:01,000
(Swan) If she ran away, they would catch her →

148
00:11:01,000 --> 00:11:03,000
Apparently this has been repeated for 8 years.

149
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:06,000
No, I heard that earlier...

150
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:10,000
Well, it's not just them that I'm running away from...

151
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:12,000
What do you mean...?

152
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:14,000
(Reporter's voice) Ma'am!

153
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:16,000
(Reporter's voice) What do you think about what your husband did?

154
00:11:16,000 --> 00:11:19,000
(Male) Come out, murderer! (Reporter) Please tell me your story. There you are!

155
00:11:23,000 --> 00:11:25,000
Yuuki this way.

156
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:32,000
Let's stay here. Hey.

157
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:37,000
(Hiroe) Mom, can I go there with Yuki?

158
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:40,000
📞(Hiroe's mother) We have a lot of reporters coming to our house, which is a problem.

159
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:42,000
At least Yuuki...

160
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:45,000
📞(Hiroe's mother) I don't want anything to do with you guys.

161
00:11:45,000 --> 00:11:47,000
mother! (sound of phone hanging up)

162
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:51,000
(Tapping sound) Kya!

163
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:56,000
(Man) Use your body to give me 100 million back. She will work for her husband until he dies.

164
00:11:56,000 --> 00:11:58,000
Ah, I'll keep the kid.

165
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:00,000
Mama! Mama!

166
00:12:00,000 --> 00:12:03,000
Don't touch it!

167
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:08,000
Let go! No! Stop it!

168
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:12,000
(Hiroe's voice) My child was being violently assaulted and I felt like I couldn't stay here...

169
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:17,000
(Hiroe) Yuki Let's go. Yeah.

170
00:12:21,000 --> 00:12:24,000
(Hiroe's voice) I had no choice but to run away from home.

171
00:12:24,000 --> 00:12:29,000
I went to a relative's house, but they found me and it was posted on the internet.

172
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:34,000
Even if I ran away to the hotel, an employee wrote.

173
00:12:34,000 --> 00:12:37,000
Leave Tokyo and run to Tochigi →

174
00:12:37,000 --> 00:12:41,000
I lived and worked at a restaurant.

175
00:12:41,000 --> 00:12:48,000
But soon it became a rumor, it was posted on the internet, and those guys showed up...

176
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:53,000
My son and I repeatedly ran away at night.

177
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:59,000
I ran away to Tohoku, but no matter where I went, I was found.

178
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:04,000
I came back knowing it was harder to find in the city.

179
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:11,000
No matter where you run, you will be found.

180
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:16,000
Yeah... a family of murderers.

181
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:24,000
(Hiroe) It was my first time speaking.

182
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:27,000
Because there was no one to listen.

183
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,000
(sound of door opening)

184
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:39,000
(Suguro) It's not something we should do. I'm going home.

185
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,000
Huh? Please wait.

186
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:44,000
Take him to the Life Safety Division. It would be nice to have two people.

187
00:13:44,000 --> 00:13:47,000
(Mio) Yes. You shouldn't have bothered to call us.

188
00:13:47,000 --> 00:13:49,000
Yes, Shiratori Special.

189
00:13:49,000 --> 00:13:52,000
(Suguro) Shall we eat and go home? Wow.

190
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:54,000
Ah, wait!

191
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:56,000
Even Snow White rice balls.

192
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,000
snow white? What do you mean?

193
00:13:58,000 --> 00:14:04,000
Maybe... When you think of ``Snow White,'' you think of a poisoned apple.

194
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:07,000
Maybe one of these is poisonous...

195
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,000
I can't leave it alone.

196
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:12,000
There was nothing in it.

197
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:16,000
I wonder if I can leave her alone too. I protected it first.

198
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:19,000
It's not our job.

199
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:22,000
I'm not poisonous either. Salt musubi is the best. (Mio) Yeah.

200
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:25,000
Consult with your local jurisdiction.

201
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:27,000
Are you abandoning me?

202
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:34,000
I'm not abandoning you. I'll have the person in charge take over.

203
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:37,000
But we are also responsible for what happened...

204
00:14:37,000 --> 00:14:43,000
A detective's job is to investigate and arrest the criminal.

205
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:46,000
Mio-nee, aren't you cold?

206
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:48,000
So what can we do?

207
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:50,000
Let's think about that.

208
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:55,000
What that person's husband did is unforgivable even if he was killed.

209
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:57,000
But it's not like the wife committed the crime...

210
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:01,000
(Suguro) My husband took care of an elementary school child.

211
00:15:01,000 --> 00:15:04,000
Family members are also destined to bear the burden of sin.

212
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:08,000
Are you serious? (Suguro) The world thinks so.

213
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:11,000
As a person... Yes, it's a question of feelings.

214
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:15,000
sympathy? Because sympathy leads to wrong judgment.

215
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:21,000
Detectives don't just arrest criminals. (Suguro) Is that it again?

216
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:24,000
Don't the police just make arrests?

217
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:27,000
We, the police, should have done something a long time ago...

218
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:32,000
If you live with that kind of logic, you will someday despair in reality.

219
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:35,000
Shouldn't you? I don't mind, but don't force yourself on others!

220
00:15:35,000 --> 00:15:37,000
No, I'm not forcing it on you!

221
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Speaking of which→

222
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:43,000
Momoko was also the cause of the internet firestorm.

223
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:45,000
I came here.

224
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:48,000
(sigh)

225
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,000
(High school girl) Don't you want to eat limited-time donuts after going to karaoke?

226
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:56,000
Eh, I want to eat it. Matcha Matcha….

227
00:15:56,000 --> 00:16:07,000
♬〜

228
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:10,000
What were you doing? Yes, show me your smartphone.

229
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,000
Huh?

230
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:14,000
Wait.

231
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:18,000
Arrested for the crime of filming sexual poses!

232
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:20,000
Let go!

233
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:22,000
Stop, you pervert!

234
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:27,000
Oh my!

235
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:30,000
Ugh... Ugh... What is it?

236
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:34,000
Please let go! Ugh...!

237
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:37,000
(Momoko's voice) In a way that is dangerous and prohibited→

238
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:39,000
I held it down.

239
00:16:39,000 --> 00:16:41,000
It was captured on video...

240
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:46,000
(Momoko's voice) It was spread on the internet and the police were criticized a lot →

241
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:49,000
Even my private life was exposed.

242
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:54,000
I started to hate everything and tried to quit the police force, but...

243
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:57,000
The manager picked it up.

244
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:00,000
(sigh)

245
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,000
(Nemoto) You guys!

246
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:11,000
Don't go on a picnic just because it's a holiday!

247
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,000
Ah, you understand this well.

248
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,000
A call was made to 110.

249
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,000
A big truck stopped →

250
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,000
Neighbors say that some unscrupulous people hang out and are a nuisance.

251
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,000
ah….

252
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,000
The rice balls are so delicious!

253
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:28,000
Oh, the chef made it for me. please.

254
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:30,000
It's a Snow White rice ball.

255
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:33,000
Hey, I'll have it. I'll clean up and go home!

256
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:38,000
My boss is telling me to come back. He was angry at me for not getting into unnecessary matters!

257
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,000
Official review officer?

258
00:17:40,000 --> 00:17:42,000
That's right.

259
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:46,000
We're like the managers in charge of the best stars.

260
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:49,000
I'll punish the selfish talent.

261
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:53,000
I told you. Listen to me and go home!

262
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:57,000
Is it obvious what we are doing? Isn't it strange?

263
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:04,000
Are you watching me?

264
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,000
(chewing sound) Ugh...!

265
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:12,000
what up?

266
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:15,000
(Masuda) I might have broken my tooth. (Nemoto) Walnut!?

267
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Where is your son?

268
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:30,000
My son and I got separated while running away.

269
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:36,000
(noise)

270
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,000
(Suguro) Did you hear something?

271
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:43,000
Yeah, noise.

272
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,000
noise?

273
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:52,000
Mom, I don't have supernatural powers or anything like that, so don't back down.

274
00:18:55,000 --> 00:19:00,000
I learned this from the maintenance professional who maintains this car.

275
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:06,000
Car engines make strange noises when they break down.

276
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:08,000
The same goes for people.

277
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:15,000
When you lie or when your mind is disturbed, you make noises.

278
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:17,000
Please listen to that carefully.

279
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:27,000
Please tell me the truth. We are allies.

280
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:35,000
This truck is called Ichibanboshi.

281
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:41,000
It's so big and conspicuous that it's said to be the ultimate idiot.→

282
00:19:41,000 --> 00:19:44,000
The first light that shines in the sky has a meaning.

283
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:46,000
It's our spirit!

284
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:53,000
Mr. Hiroe?

285
00:19:59,000 --> 00:20:05,000
Eight years ago, I entrusted my child to a child guidance center in Taito Ward.

286
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:08,000
What about contact? (Hiroe) I have never taken one.

287
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:10,000
Now I'm 16 years old...

288
00:20:12,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Chief, let's go.

289
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:23,000
Well, if you just take this person with you. (Swan) Huh?

290
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,000
Please drive the chef.

291
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:28,000
However, there was an order to come back...

292
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:31,000
Chef: It's a ship we've boarded!

293
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:35,000
Momoko-san, this truck is not a taxi.

294
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:39,000
I'm sorry, but I can't drive. Excuse me.

295
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,000
It's cold!

296
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:54,000
♬〜

297
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:56,000
Hey, don't take your eyes off this truck.

298
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,000
(3 people) Yes.

299
00:20:59,000 --> 00:21:02,000
We agree. Unusual.

300
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:05,000
Then... we have no choice but to date!

301
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,000
Why!

302
00:21:38,000 --> 00:21:44,000
(Director) Yes, I remember. It was a cold winter day.

303
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:48,000
It is true that we took an 8-year-old boy into our care.

304
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:55,000
(Director) I was crying alone in front of the entrance.

305
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:59,000
I asked him what happened, but he didn't want to talk →

306
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,000
Leave it here for a while →

307
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:04,000
After that, he went to a children's home.

308
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:09,000
So, is Yuki-kun still in that facility?

309
00:22:09,000 --> 00:22:14,000
(Director) No. Was it 3 months ago?

310
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:20,000
On the day I graduated from junior high school, I suddenly disappeared somewhere.

311
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:26,000
(Staff) Yuki-kun's personal belongings. I received it from the facility.

312
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:30,000
Is it Yuuki-kun's?

313
00:22:34,000 --> 00:22:38,000
(Hiroe) I wore this that night...

314
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:46,000
♬〜

315
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:48,000
(Hiroe) Sit here.

316
00:22:55,000 --> 00:22:57,000
Yuuki...

317
00:22:58,000 --> 00:23:00,000
(Yuki) It's cold.

318
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:09,000
Warm.

319
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:15,000
Listen.

320
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:23,000
Mama and Yuuki will be living in hiding from now on.

321
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:27,000
If you're with your mom, you'll be called a murderer.

322
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:30,000
What will a debt collector do if he finds out?

323
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:35,000
The police won't help me.

324
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:39,000
So is that okay? Yuuki.

325
00:23:39,000 --> 00:23:43,000
From now on, we will live separately.

326
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:45,000
Mom?

327
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:48,000
(Hiroe) Mama and Yuki will become strangers.

328
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:53,000
I won't contact you again.

329
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:58,000
You can't find me either.

330
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:01,000
Mama! (Hiroe) It's for survival.

331
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:08,000
Mom, where are you going? Don't go!

332
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,000
Don't come!

333
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:16,000
♬〜

334
00:24:16,000 --> 00:24:19,000
Goodbye.

335
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:24,000
Mama! Mama!

336
00:24:33,000 --> 00:24:35,000
Are you still relieved?

337
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,000
Let's search for my son together.

338
00:24:37,000 --> 00:24:40,000
I'm sorry, but once the criminal is caught, the detective's job is over.

339
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:43,000
Huh? Forget this person?

340
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:45,000
I can't do that!

341
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:49,000
Once the culprit is caught, the incident will be forgotten. Our job is to repeat that.

342
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:52,000
I don't want to forget! This person did nothing wrong!

343
00:24:52,000 --> 00:24:57,000
There are many more people suffering from this kind of damage. We need to hear your voice before it becomes an incident!

344
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,000
If you want to say something beautiful, become a politician!

345
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:01,000
I get off.

346
00:25:01,000 --> 00:25:04,000
Was Kuro-san that kind of person?

347
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:06,000
I have something to do with my daughter.

348
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:10,000
If I do something unnecessary and get punished, my career as a detective will be over.

349
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:17,000
(Suguro) Mom, I'm sorry.

350
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:19,000
Mr. Kuro!

351
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:21,000
(sigh)

352
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:28,000
Mio-nee too?

353
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:33,000
Mio-nee is busy studying.

354
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:35,000
Huh?

355
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:41,000
Reference book for the national civil service examination.

356
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:45,000
yes. I'm always reading it in secret.

357
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:49,000
Come out.

358
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:53,000
Why did you study to become a career member?

359
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:58,000
(Mio) I will stay.

360
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:01,000
Even though I'm against it, why?

361
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:06,000
I have to be here.

362
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:08,000
yeah?

363
00:26:08,000 --> 00:26:12,000
(Mio) Ah... Chief: Let's finish this.

364
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:17,000
There are three people, including myself, who are against continuing this way. 3 to 3.

365
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:20,000
But we have a responsibility to follow the orders above.

366
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:23,000
The vote was 4 to 3, with orders counted as one vote.

367
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:26,000
It's settled.

368
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:32,000
There are seven detectives in my house.

369
00:26:32,000 --> 00:26:37,000
♬〜

370
00:26:53,924 --> 00:26:56,924
(Buds/Momoko) Ah! (Souichiro Midorikawa) What?

371
00:26:56,924 --> 00:26:58,924
The mechanical guy I talked about earlier.

372
00:27:01,924 --> 00:27:04,924
Momoko: I came even though it was my day off. Please lend me money.

373
00:27:04,924 --> 00:27:06,924
A new machine is about to come out.

374
00:27:06,924 --> 00:27:09,924
There's still a lot left. Give it back first.

375
00:27:09,924 --> 00:27:11,924
Is that so? Yeah.

376
00:27:11,924 --> 00:27:16,924
Mecha old man... You asked for the information. Please let me know your opinion.

377
00:27:16,924 --> 00:27:19,924
(Midorikawa) Give me coffee. Understood.

378
00:27:20,924 --> 00:27:27,924
I've been in the police force for 40 years. Several people met with the families of the perpetrators.

379
00:27:27,924 --> 00:27:30,924
I still have some regrets.

380
00:27:30,924 --> 00:27:34,924
In one incident, I protected the perpetrator's family.

381
00:27:34,924 --> 00:27:38,924
The family's son murdered a neighbor's child.

382
00:27:38,924 --> 00:27:44,924
I was chased by reporters, and no matter where I ran, my whereabouts were exposed.

383
00:27:44,924 --> 00:27:47,924
Dad feels extremely responsible.

384
00:27:47,924 --> 00:27:51,924
I was ordered to keep my father safe.

385
00:27:51,924 --> 00:27:53,924
I wondered why I would do such a job.

386
00:27:53,924 --> 00:27:57,924
Why would you protect a criminal's family? That's it.

387
00:27:57,924 --> 00:28:03,924
However, before I could take my eyes off him, he hanged himself in the toilet.

388
00:28:04,924 --> 00:28:07,924
I couldn't protect you.

389
00:28:08,924 --> 00:28:11,924
Then you understand how I feel!

390
00:28:11,924 --> 00:28:15,924
Mecha old man, let's search for my son together.

391
00:28:15,924 --> 00:28:17,924
No, I'm against it.

392
00:28:17,924 --> 00:28:19,924
Huh? Huh?

393
00:28:21,924 --> 00:28:24,924
Sorry. It's none of your business.

394
00:28:27,924 --> 00:28:30,924
Manager-san, you're told to come back from above, right?

395
00:28:30,924 --> 00:28:32,924
Then go back.

396
00:28:32,924 --> 00:28:36,924
If you cause a problem here, you won't be able to return to the field.

397
00:28:38,924 --> 00:28:41,924
You have something to do.

398
00:28:41,924 --> 00:28:44,924
You want to settle what happened two years ago.

399
00:28:44,924 --> 00:28:47,924
For me, that was 20 years ago.

400
00:28:50,924 --> 00:28:53,924
The prey is the same.

401
00:28:57,924 --> 00:28:59,924
What are you talking about?

402
00:29:02,924 --> 00:29:04,924
Mr. Hiroe?

403
00:29:05,924 --> 00:29:07,924
Huh?

404
00:29:12,924 --> 00:29:14,924
(Man) Get on, hey.

405
00:29:15,924 --> 00:29:17,924
Hiroe-san!? Let that person go!

406
00:29:19,924 --> 00:29:21,924
stop! a little bit…!

407
00:29:21,924 --> 00:29:23,924
Hey!

408
00:29:26,924 --> 00:29:29,924
(brake sound)

409
00:29:29,924 --> 00:29:32,924
Alright! Good brakes!

410
00:29:32,924 --> 00:29:34,924
Maintenance OK!

411
00:29:35,924 --> 00:29:38,924
What the hell are you talking about? Oh my!

412
00:29:38,924 --> 00:29:40,924
Ah!

413
00:29:41,924 --> 00:29:43,924
Wow! Let me go!

414
00:29:46,924 --> 00:29:48,924
Wow! Nice shot!

415
00:29:48,924 --> 00:29:52,924
Oh my! Okay! Ah! That's an amazing shirt.

416
00:29:52,924 --> 00:29:55,924
Ahhh... Wow! Oh my!

417
00:29:55,924 --> 00:29:57,924
Go quickly!

418
00:30:04,924 --> 00:30:06,924
Why did you go outside?

419
00:30:08,924 --> 00:30:11,924
I'm protecting you! But why!?

420
00:30:12,924 --> 00:30:15,924
If this continues, it will cause trouble for everyone...

421
00:30:15,924 --> 00:30:20,924
Why would she ask the police for help even though her husband had killed someone?

422
00:30:20,924 --> 00:30:24,924
I have a responsibility too. I can't help it even if I get criticized.

423
00:30:24,924 --> 00:30:26,924
No matter what happens to me...

424
00:30:26,924 --> 00:30:28,924
Don't give in to other people's voices!

425
00:30:29,924 --> 00:30:33,924
My son is alive. Can I be left alone?

426
00:30:33,924 --> 00:30:35,924
Because they are a family of murderers!

427
00:30:35,924 --> 00:30:37,924
Don't say it like that!

428
00:30:41,924 --> 00:30:45,924
Find Section Chief Yuki-kun.

429
00:30:45,924 --> 00:30:51,924
♬〜

430
00:30:51,924 --> 00:30:54,924
Bud, please stop.

431
00:30:54,924 --> 00:30:56,924
yes.

432
00:31:10,924 --> 00:31:12,924
Ah, hello.

433
00:31:14,924 --> 00:31:18,924
Mahoro, are you angry? I said let's play together.

434
00:31:19,924 --> 00:31:23,924
It seems like you liked the game. I forgot that my dad invited me.

435
00:31:23,924 --> 00:31:26,924
📞Hahahaha… I see.

436
00:31:27,924 --> 00:31:30,924
Ah, that...

437
00:31:32,924 --> 00:31:38,924
What if… What if →

438
00:31:38,924 --> 00:31:42,924
If I suddenly disappear →

439
00:31:42,924 --> 00:31:48,924
How do you and Mahoro feel?

440
00:31:49,924 --> 00:31:54,924
You must be tired. Dad needs a break.

441
00:31:55,924 --> 00:31:59,924
Ah... haha ​​That's right.

442
00:32:01,924 --> 00:32:03,924
📞I heard something strange.

443
00:32:04,924 --> 00:32:08,924
I'll be sad when you're gone.

444
00:32:08,924 --> 00:32:11,924
How should I live with Mahoro?

445
00:32:12,924 --> 00:32:14,924
Sorry, sorry.

446
00:32:14,924 --> 00:32:16,924
Because that's not the case.

447
00:32:18,924 --> 00:32:21,924
Are you confused about work?

448
00:32:23,924 --> 00:32:25,924
...Well.

449
00:32:26,924 --> 00:32:30,924
📞(Shiori) I may not be able to push myself because I'm the section chief →

450
00:32:30,924 --> 00:32:33,924
When I was in the second section→

451
00:32:33,924 --> 00:32:36,924
I love how you were always aggressive and aggressive.

452
00:32:40,924 --> 00:32:43,924
Well then, good luck with your work.

453
00:32:45,924 --> 00:32:48,924
thank you. See you then.

454
00:32:48,924 --> 00:33:05,924
♬〜

455
00:33:05,924 --> 00:33:07,924
Manager: No!

456
00:33:08,924 --> 00:33:11,924
Search for Yuki-kun. There might be some clues.

457
00:33:11,924 --> 00:33:13,924
Part-time job information magazine?

458
00:33:13,924 --> 00:33:16,924
The page is folded and checked. Many!

459
00:33:16,924 --> 00:33:19,924
Maybe he works somewhere in this store.

460
00:33:19,924 --> 00:33:26,924
♬〜

461
00:33:26,924 --> 00:33:30,924
Didn't someone named Yuki Nakamura work part-time at this store?

462
00:33:30,924 --> 00:33:32,924
I'm a 16-year-old child.

463
00:33:32,924 --> 00:33:35,924
No, I'm not working.

464
00:33:35,924 --> 00:33:37,924
is that so. thank you.

465
00:33:40,924 --> 00:33:44,924
Isn't there a boy named Yuki Nakamura working at your shop?

466
00:33:44,924 --> 00:33:48,924
Ah, that's right... my part-time job...

467
00:33:48,924 --> 00:33:50,924
Help your mom too. yes.

468
00:33:50,924 --> 00:33:52,924
here. Understood. Excuse me.

469
00:33:54,924 --> 00:33:57,924
Well then, I guess I'll go here.

470
00:33:58,924 --> 00:34:00,924
This is Amao.

471
00:34:00,924 --> 00:34:04,924
Isn't there a man named Yuki Nakamura working here?

472
00:34:04,924 --> 00:34:06,924
I don't work at my house.

473
00:34:06,924 --> 00:34:08,924
thank you. thank you.

474
00:34:08,924 --> 00:34:10,924
Let's go next.

475
00:34:15,924 --> 00:34:19,924
There wasn't. Let's go to this store next time.

476
00:34:19,924 --> 00:34:21,924
There are still over a dozen stores checked.

477
00:34:21,924 --> 00:34:24,924
Yeah. Some places are far away...

478
00:34:24,924 --> 00:34:26,924
Even if I do all this, when will I be able to meet you again?

479
00:34:28,924 --> 00:34:32,924
Chief: The Deputy Chief Cabinet Secretary ordered the investigation to be halted.

480
00:34:38,924 --> 00:34:41,924
Please tell me.

481
00:34:41,924 --> 00:34:44,924
I will accept the punishment graciously.

482
00:34:44,924 --> 00:34:47,924
Bud: Let's go to this store. Ask me to drive.

483
00:34:47,924 --> 00:34:49,924
yes!

484
00:34:49,924 --> 00:34:51,924
🔊(Swan) This is my place.

485
00:34:53,924 --> 00:34:56,924
This handle cannot be given to anyone else.

486
00:34:56,924 --> 00:35:11,924
♬〜

487
00:35:11,924 --> 00:35:13,924
🔊(Suguro) Hey!

488
00:35:14,924 --> 00:35:17,924
You guys are idiots →

489
00:35:17,924 --> 00:35:20,924
I'm a big idiot!

490
00:35:20,924 --> 00:35:22,924
Mr. Kuro...

491
00:35:22,924 --> 00:35:24,924
🔊(Suguro) I beat up the men who were chasing me.

492
00:35:24,924 --> 00:35:26,924
🔊I broke my mouth!

493
00:35:26,924 --> 00:35:29,924
They were also looking for their son. Part-time job: I understand.

494
00:35:29,924 --> 00:35:32,924
Follow me, Ichibanboshi!

495
00:35:32,924 --> 00:35:37,924
♬〜

496
00:35:37,924 --> 00:35:40,924
Kuu!

497
00:35:41,924 --> 00:35:43,924
(Tsubomi and Momoko's laughter)

498
00:35:45,924 --> 00:35:53,924
(siren)

499
00:35:53,924 --> 00:36:02,924
♬〜

500
00:36:02,924 --> 00:36:04,924
Apparently he works at the Ferris wheel.

501
00:36:04,924 --> 00:36:09,924
Apparently the men came from time to time to keep watch. Wait for mom to show up.

502
00:36:09,924 --> 00:36:11,924
Let's go.

503
00:36:14,924 --> 00:36:16,924
(cheerful voice)

504
00:36:18,924 --> 00:36:22,924
(Hiroe) A long time ago, I came to visit with my family...

505
00:36:22,924 --> 00:36:25,924
Yuki-kun, you remember.

506
00:36:26,924 --> 00:36:28,924
We will expose debt collectors.

507
00:36:28,924 --> 00:36:33,924
From now on, we will never live apart. We will be your strength.

508
00:36:33,924 --> 00:36:36,924
How can I say thank you...

509
00:36:38,924 --> 00:36:59,924
♬〜

510
00:36:59,924 --> 00:37:20,924
♬〜

511
00:37:20,924 --> 00:37:25,924
There aren't any. I'll ask you. Yeah.

512
00:37:25,924 --> 00:37:31,924
Um...maybe you're Nakamura Yuuki's mother?

513
00:37:31,924 --> 00:37:34,924
Huh... yes. But why me?

514
00:37:34,924 --> 00:37:36,924
Please wait a moment.

515
00:37:50,924 --> 00:37:52,924
Something that Yuki-kun has entrusted to me...

516
00:37:54,924 --> 00:37:56,924
When my mom comes, please give it to me.

517
00:38:04,924 --> 00:38:23,924
♬〜

518
00:38:23,924 --> 00:38:26,924
(Hiroe's voice) To my mother.

519
00:38:26,924 --> 00:38:30,924
Mom, if you are reading this, then →

520
00:38:30,924 --> 00:38:33,924
You came to pick me up.

521
00:38:33,924 --> 00:38:35,924
I've been waiting.

522
00:38:35,924 --> 00:38:39,924
I thought we'd meet someday.

523
00:38:39,924 --> 00:38:44,924
Today is 8 years and 75 days since we broke up.

524
00:38:44,924 --> 00:38:47,924
(Hiroe and Yuki's voices) Sorry for being so detailed.

525
00:38:47,924 --> 00:38:50,924
(Yuki's voice) I've never felt lonely.

526
00:38:50,924 --> 00:38:54,924
Even if we couldn't meet, you were always by my side.

527
00:38:54,924 --> 00:38:57,924
Mom has always protected me.

528
00:38:57,924 --> 00:39:00,924
But, mom→

529
00:39:00,924 --> 00:39:04,924
I also made a friend that I want to protect.

530
00:39:06,924 --> 00:39:10,924
(Yuki's voice) He's a kid who came here alone to play.

531
00:39:10,924 --> 00:39:14,924
He was the same age and was alone like me.

532
00:39:16,924 --> 00:39:20,924
(Yuki's voice) He said he left home because his parents had done something to him...

533
00:39:20,924 --> 00:39:28,924
♬〜

534
00:39:28,924 --> 00:39:34,924
(Yuki's voice) When I said I was cold, that child held my hand and rubbed it.

535
00:39:34,924 --> 00:39:37,924
It was warm.

536
00:39:37,924 --> 00:39:40,924
Mom, did you understand?

537
00:39:40,924 --> 00:39:42,924
Warm.

538
00:39:43,924 --> 00:39:47,924
(Yuki's voice) Yes, she did the same thing as my mother.

539
00:39:47,924 --> 00:39:53,924
♬〜

540
00:39:53,924 --> 00:39:56,924
(Yuki's voice) That child looks just like her mother.

541
00:39:56,924 --> 00:40:02,924
♬〜

542
00:40:02,924 --> 00:40:07,924
(Yuki's voice) I'm going somewhere far away with that child.

543
00:40:07,924 --> 00:40:11,924
We decided to work together somewhere.

544
00:40:11,924 --> 00:40:19,924
♬〜

545
00:40:19,924 --> 00:40:23,924
(Yuki's voice) So don't search anymore. You don't have to worry anymore.

546
00:40:23,924 --> 00:40:26,924
I can walk alone.

547
00:40:26,924 --> 00:40:34,924
♬〜

548
00:40:34,924 --> 00:40:37,924
(Yuki's voice) Thank you for today.

549
00:40:37,924 --> 00:40:42,924
I'm my mother's child no matter where I go. From Yuki.

550
00:40:44,924 --> 00:40:46,924
(sob)

551
00:40:46,924 --> 00:40:48,924
Yuuki...

552
00:40:48,924 --> 00:40:56,924
♬〜

553
00:40:56,924 --> 00:41:01,924
Before I knew it, my son became an adult...

554
00:41:01,924 --> 00:41:22,924
♬〜

555
00:41:24,924 --> 00:41:30,924
♬〜

556
00:41:30,924 --> 00:41:32,924
(Man) Stop it!

557
00:41:32,924 --> 00:41:36,924
(Nemoto) I'll give you the ``Rokupo Zensho'' so you can read it from cover to cover!

558
00:41:36,924 --> 00:41:38,924
Because my husband borrowed money →

559
00:41:38,924 --> 00:41:42,924
There is no obligation to pay to your family unless you are a joint guarantor!

560
00:41:42,924 --> 00:41:44,924
(Masuda) Threatening towards his wife →

561
00:41:44,924 --> 00:41:48,924
We will thoroughly investigate your missing husband!

562
00:41:49,924 --> 00:41:57,924
♬〜

563
00:41:58,924 --> 00:42:00,924
(Everyone laughs)

564
00:42:02,924 --> 00:42:06,924
(Suguro) Good evening. If you don't mind, this is Patota from the National Police Agency.

565
00:42:07,924 --> 00:42:11,924
(applause)

566
00:42:11,924 --> 00:42:13,924
Oh...!

567
00:42:17,924 --> 00:42:19,924
Momoko-san!

568
00:42:19,924 --> 00:42:22,924
Hey... you're getting too carried away!

569
00:42:22,924 --> 00:42:27,924
Ah! It hurts! ah….

570
00:42:27,924 --> 00:42:30,924
♬〜(Swan) “I was scared of boredom.”

571
00:42:30,924 --> 00:42:32,924
♬~ “I ran away into the darkness of the night…”

572
00:42:32,924 --> 00:42:34,924
(Together) Angel!

573
00:42:34,924 --> 00:42:37,924
Hey! We... we're like...

574
00:42:37,924 --> 00:42:39,924
what? what? I feel like an outcast.

575
00:42:39,924 --> 00:42:41,924
(Together) Angel!

576
00:42:41,924 --> 00:42:44,924
♬〜(Swan) “Can you master baby? Master baby!”

577
00:42:45,924 --> 00:42:55,924
♬〜

578
00:43:06,924 --> 00:43:21,924
♬〜

579
00:43:21,924 --> 00:43:29,924
♬〜

580
00:43:29,924 --> 00:43:35,924
♬〜

581
00:43:35,924 --> 00:43:37,924
(knock)

582
00:43:37,924 --> 00:43:39,924
please.

583
00:43:39,924 --> 00:43:51,924
♬〜

584
00:43:51,924 --> 00:43:53,924
I went to receive the punishment.

585
00:43:53,924 --> 00:43:57,924
I realize that I did something unnecessary.

586
00:43:57,924 --> 00:44:07,924
♬〜

587
00:44:07,924 --> 00:44:11,924
We have completely opposite ways of thinking.

588
00:44:14,924 --> 00:44:19,924
My daughter is happy. Thank you for the game console.

589
00:44:21,924 --> 00:44:23,924
Brother.

590
00:44:23,924 --> 00:44:29,924
♬〜
